    <section class="font-body text-on-surface leading-relaxed space-y-6">
      <p>Malaysia's food delivery industry has exploded — from cloud kitchens in Cheras and KL to catering businesses serving the Klang Valley, demand for reliable, food-safe packaging is at an all-time high. Yet many F&B operators make costly packaging mistakes: boxes that collapse under heat, wrong sizes that waste space, or flimsy single-ply cartons that leak or crush en route. Choosing the right carton box from the start protects your food, your brand, and your reputation.</p>

      <p>At Quinocycle Sdn. Bhd. in Balakong, Selangor, we supply wholesale corrugated carton boxes to businesses across Peninsular Malaysia — including hundreds of F&B operators, caterers, and cloud kitchens. This guide breaks down exactly what to look for when buying carton boxes for food delivery use.</p>

      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">Why Box Construction Matters in F&B Packaging</h2>
      <p>Not all carton boxes are equal. The food delivery environment introduces unique stresses: temperature fluctuations from hot meals, moisture from condensation, stacking in delivery bags, and handling by multiple people. These factors degrade low-grade boxes quickly.</p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">Single Wall vs Double Wall</h3>
      <p>Single wall (SW) corrugated boxes — made from three layers of board — are light and cost-effective. They work well for dry goods, baked items, individual meal kits, or lightweight packaged products. Double wall (DW) boxes, with five layers, offer significantly greater stacking strength and moisture resistance, making them ideal for heavier multi-portion meal delivery or cold chain outer packaging.</p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">B Flute vs C Flute for F&B</h3>
      <p>B flute boards are thinner but offer better puncture resistance — excellent for tightly stacked delivery runs. C flute provides higher compressive strength and cushioning, making it better for bulkier meal packs or catering trays. BC double wall combines both, giving you the best of both worlds for premium delivery operations.</p>

      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">Recommended Box Sizes for F&B Delivery in KL & Selangor</h2>
      <p>Getting the sizing right reduces material waste and prevents products from shifting in transit. Here are the configurations we recommend most for F&B businesses:</p>

      <div class="bg-surface-variant/50 border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-2xl p-6 my-8">
