      <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mt-10 mb-4">Hygiene Considerations for Food-Adjacent Packaging</h2>
      <p>While corrugated carton boxes are not designed for direct food contact, they can still affect food safety when used improperly. When you buy new carton boxes from Quinocycle, you receive unused boxes in clean condition — never recycled materials mixed with unknown contaminants.</p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">Line Boxes When Needed</h3>
      <p>For warm or liquid-adjacent foods, line your carton boxes with food-grade PE liners or aluminium foil inserts. This protects the box from moisture weakening while keeping contents secure. The outer corrugated shell then acts as a rigid, stackable transport layer.</p>

      <h3 class="font-headline text-xl font-semibold text-on-surface mt-6 mb-3">Storage and Humidity Control</h3>
      <p>Store your carton box supply in a dry, covered area away from direct sunlight. Moisture is corrugated cardboard's biggest enemy — even a humid warehouse corner can reduce box compressive strength by 30% or more. Raised pallets and covered storage are best practice.</p>

